		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I got the HQ2X/3X/4X scaling working now and made an example video of the HQ3X at 720p.  I cannot record 1080p unfortunately so I can't capture the 4X one in video.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B_v5vvh2h0A">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B_v5vvh2h0A</a><!-- m --><br /><br />There's no audio because I needed the room for the scaler.   Because space constraints have been hit, I am going to stuff another board with a bigger part that fortunately has the same pinout, hopefully alleviating my space issues.<br /><br />With this bigger part, I should be able to get VRC7 in there too. (VRC7 is around 1300 LEs, while the HQX scaler is 2230 and the 65C02 core is 1320).

		

