	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>kevtris</b> [ Thu Nov 20, 2014 3:19 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Hi-Def NES HDMI Adapter for the NES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">kevtris wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">65C02 core<br /></div>Any potential problems there with unofficial instructions?</div><br /><br />no, this is my &quot;hypervisor&quot; CPU that sits on the FPGA.  it does not run the game code, it only runs my code that sits on the FPGA itself.  this CPU runs the menu and hardware initialization and such.  The NES CPU still is running the actual game code.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


